In early March 1918, he organized the First Lugansk Socialist Detachment, which defended the city of Kharkov from the German-Austrian troops. Civil War[edit | edit code]
During the Civil War, he was commander of the Koryak group of Soviet troops in the Far East, deputy commander and member of the Military Council of the Far Eastern Front. One of the organizers and member of the Revolutionary Military Council of the Far Eastern Republic. First chairman of the executive committee of the district SDT [edit | edit code]
1923-1926 - Secretary of the Karaginsky Village Council
1926-1931